Her loss underscores the widespread discontent among voters with her policies and the party's leadership, as evidenced by the "slow hand claps" she received upon her departure. name: Copa
summary: Canada's national soccer team has advanced to the quarterfinals of the Copa America tournament after playing Chile to a 0-0 draw. This is the first time Canada has reached this stage in the competition. The team will now face Venezuela in the next round. Despite not scoring against Chile, Canada's goalkeeper, Maxime Crepeau, from Quebec, was instrumental in the team's success by making several key saves. Meanwhile, Chile's Humberto Suazo was sent off in the first half for a red card. Argentina also advanced to the quarterfinals after overcoming a scare against Ecuador, while the matchups for the 2024 Copa America quarterfinals have been officially set.
